er the target test source root, and modifications to build.gradle aren't allowed. \\n\\nCould I add a test source that modifies Jacoco at runtime? But it seems the report is generated after the test JVM exits, so how could I handle that? Maybe I could write a test that edits the Jacoco report directly, but that’s tricky. Using shadow classes is forbidden too, and I need to be mindful of those restrictions. There’s just so much to consider here!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing Jacoco coverage and methods**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether it can list call sites included in the native image after the test code references a method. If the frame for that method has no line number, I’m wondering how it can mark anything as covered. It seems impossible with the current logic. \\n\\nThe user might expect patch tests, but I need to focus on the active class. I’m considering if I could invoke class$ through Groovy’s MOP differently to improve Jacoco method coverage. I’ll look closely at the Jacoco XML for AssertionSupport$5 and check if there are lines for doubleStar shouldEscape, but also the report line. This is tricky!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_d8bzETgXZZALwTBUL8JfTCSM|fc_0eb937ad0b8287a0016a1170dccce8819588568ff32a8ca5a3", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\np='tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured-common/5.5.0/build/reports/jacoco/test/jacocoTestReport.xml'\nroot=ET.parse(p).getroot()\nfor pkg in root.findall('package'):\n  if pkg.get('name')=='io/restassured/internal/common/assertion':\n    for cls in pkg.findall('class'):\n      if cls.get('name').endswith('AssertionSupport$5') or cls.get('name').endswith('AssertionSupport'):\n        print('CLASS', cls.get('name'), cls.get('sourcefilename'))\n        for m in cls.findall('method'):\n          print(' ', m.get('name'), m.get('desc'), m.get('line'), [(c.get('type'),c.get('missed'),c.get('covered')) for c in m.findall('counter')])\n    for sf in pkg.findall('sourcefile'):\n      if sf.get('name')=='AssertionSupport.groovy':\n        print('SOURCE', sf.get('name'))\n        for line in sf.findall('line'):\n          print(' ', line.attrib)\nPY", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 694, "output": 652, "cacheRead": 50688, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 52034, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779527889759, "responseId": "resp_0eb937ad0b8287a0016a1170d25cf48195a0821b22b32261fe"}}
